						<summary>

						<p>North wall of the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Mantrapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Māṟavarman [Parākrama]-pāṇḍya: year 26: 1361 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This incomplete inscription may be assigned to c. 14th century on palaeographical considerations.</p>						

						<p>It records a deed of agreement on the sale of tax-free <hi rend="italic">(iṟaiyili)</hi> lands made over to the Ādichaṇḍēśvaradēvakaṉmigaḷ of the temple of Tiruvuśāttāṉam-uḍaiya-ṉāyaṉār of Uśāttāṉam <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Kēraḷakulāśaṉichchaturvēdimaṅgalam in [Puṟaṅ]karambai-nāḍu, in Rājē[ndraśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu*]. Vāḻavandanallūr is stated to be a <hi rend="italic">tirunāmattukkāṇi</hi> village in the western side of Rājēndraśōḻapērēri. The details are not clear as the record is damaged in some places.</p>						

						</summary>
